  "text": "The simple analytical theory presented in this paper reproduces the qualitative behavior and the order of magnitude of the heat fluxes computed through a nonlinear numerical model with zero synoptic wind [CITATION_1] . It also provides a framework which, when combined with the parameterization procedure introduced by [CITATION_2] using a nonlinear model, can be used to develop a general procedure to parameterize mesoscale effects for use in general circulation and numerical weather prediction models.",
